me around 50 or so tries with so many stacks of star rubies<br>
for banishment used up at around 85pp per ruby before I <br>
finally got flagged a couple days ago.  My group barely made<br>
it through the trials with me at lev63, 65 war, 65 mage,<br>
61 chanter, 60 cleric, 62 necro.  4 group members died in<br>
the final round with me going oom at the final nuke. The<br>
trial was done fully buffed with kei, virtue, me on horse with<br>
ft4 and a bunch of aa skills used as well as having banished<br>
2 rock guys successfully which never happens since banish<br>
gets resisted at least 2 out of 3 tries.<br>
<br>
The trials aren't easy even if you're high level with great equip<br>
and a bunch of aa.  I wouldn't recommend anyone below 60 to<br>
even attempt the trials because even if by some miracle you<br>
pass, you can forget about getting a pickup group in PoS &amp;<br>
PoV.  The mobs there are very high level and it's tough for a<br>
caster below 60 to land any spells and even tougher for <br>
melees below 60 to stay alive when you're being quadded for<br>
600 &amp; enraged on.<br>
<br>
So my advice is not to give up if you're 60+ and still trying to<br>
pass the trials.  If you're below 60, I wouldn't recommend the<br>
trials unless you want a little bit of xp and a shot at some<br>
decent loot while doing the trials.<br>
<br>
For those of you who are feeling a bit frustrated because you<br>
think no one in the guild wants to help you get flagged, I can<br>
personally say from experience that I have seen many flagged<br>
guildies help out with the trials on a regular basis donating <br>
hours of their time, plat, countless deaths and xp to help <br>
others get flagged.  Everyone 60+ will be flagged in time.<br>
